لَّمَا تَعَمَّقْتُ فِي ٱلقَضِيَّةِ بَحْثًا عَنْ دَلِيلٍ يَقْضِي بِبَراءَتِك، وَجَدْتُ مَزِيدًا مِنَ ٱلْأَدِلَّةِ ٱلْقَوِيَّةِ ٱلَّتِي تُدِينُك","english":"Detective Conan"},{"text":"ادانت غرفة عمليات محاربة تنظيم داعش الإرهابي صبراتة بأشد العبارات العمل الإرهابي الجبان الذي أودي بحياة ستة و ثلاثون فردا في مدينة الأبيار.","english":"The Cell of Operations of War against the terrorist formation Daesh of Sabrata has condemned with harsh words the cowardly terrorist action by which thirty-six individuals in the town of Al-Abyār have lost their lives."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʔa.daː.na/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13581","headword_ar":"ادان","root":"dyn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_idaAnapN","text_ar":"اـِدَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as an intrans. v.: see 1, in the former half of the paragraph, in three places. ―         -b2-  As a trans. v.: see 1, in the latter half of the paragraph, in four places. ―         -b3-  [The following significations, namely, “ Subegit, ” and “ Pensavit, ” assigned to this verb by Golius as on the authority of the KL, and “ Voluit sibi esse servum, ” and “ Servum cepit, ” followed by an accus., assigned to it by him as on the authority of the S, I do not find in either of those works.]"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n13584","headword_ar":"اِدَّانَ","root":"dyn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AidotaAna","text_ar":"اِدْتَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, in six places."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}